      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARLO GAMBINO NZ (7) has recorded two wins and two minor placings from the past five starts. Performed well once again when second at his latest appearance over 1740m at Riverina Paceway, beaten 4 metres. Should enjoy a nice smother from this draw and will be looking for a split at some stage. Has the class to take care of this field. JIMMY JAMES MAGUIRE NZ (8) finished second last start over 1720m at Young, beaten a head. That was an improvement on the unplaced effort at Menangle the run before. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row. Finds a nice race and can find winning form. CORBIE STUMBLER (4) last appeared when sixth over 1609m at Menangle six months ago. Look out for any positive market movement. SCARED STIFF NZ (6) last appeared when seventh over 1740m at Riverina Paceway three-and-a-half months ago. Expect a better effort to kick off this prep.",
